<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-25T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-25T21:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/3–2649: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-26T10:00:00+08:00">March 26,
                                1949—10 a. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received March 26—4:23 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>655. Deptel 354, March 17. Military estimates [that] since September 1, 1948,
                        Communists have effectively integrated in own forces 210,000 troops which
                        could be used as combatant troops, including disaffected units and those
                        surrendered at Peiping. In addition Communists may have maximum of 400,000
                        captured Nationalist troops being used as replacements or service
                        forces.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>